    "inheritance_pattern": "autosomal dominant",
    "disease_category": null,
    "status": "published",
    "full_name": "Pre-mRNA processing factor 31",
    "patient_population": "Unknown",
    "treatment_status": "No current treatment; complications can be managed.",
    "eye_health_strategies": "—",
    "plain_english_summary": "PRPF31 is part of the spliceosome, the cellular machinery that processes mRNA. It is a common cause of autosomal dominant RP and is notable for 'incomplete penetrance' — some people who carry a disease-causing mutation never develop symptoms, which is why symptom-free carriers are often found within affected families."
